node.text:
These gravity boots are the best things I’ve come across in a long time! I’ve had severe editor’s posture syndrome (back pain) for years & am always looking for something to alleviate the pain. You can only go so far with yoga, but this fully decompresses your spine like nothing else.

If you have a bulging disk, sciatica, scoliosis, or just want to improve your flexibility and take care of your spine, there is nothing I recommend more than inversion.

Get 10% off Gravity Boots or anything from Teeter by clicking the link in my bio and use code: “LIVEBETTER”

node.text:
This is what I’ve spent the majority of the past 6 months working on. Researching, experimenting, editing, writing, and applying all these new rigorous habits to my everyday life.
.
‘Superhuman’ is all about helping you discover your hidden capabilities. To assist you with the tools, knowledge, and fearlessness needed to begin this exciting journey of self development so that you can ultimately go out and live a more adventurous and fulfilling life. If you want to optimize your mind & body and learn more about nutrition, fitness, biohacking, and all forms of personal growth, this podcast is for you!
.
Download Spotify and follow my podcast “SuperHuman” linked in bio! Spotify is free and easy to use!

node.text:
In order to live a prime lifestyle, we have to prime our mind, bodies, and everyday habits. I spend the majority of each day ultimately preparing myself to “become creative” so that I can prolong my flow-state and squeeze out as much innovation as possible. When there is no more juice left it’s time to rest & repair which usually concludes with escaping from the day’s rigorous activities. Enjoying @NetflixPH before sleeping is one of my favorite ways to wind down, which is now made easy with @livesmart!
.

Back home with my hummingbird friends! Health and family will be my main priority for the rest of the year, and being back is always a time for me to step back, reflect, and remember what’s most important.
.
I’m ready to relax, rejuvenate, and remind myself why I continue to #LiveBetter. Stay protected and be proactive with @aiaphilamlife for endless peace of mind!

node.text: There are only a handful of people you’ll ever meet in your life that can get you so overly excited every single time you see them. Someone who carries so much energy, fun, and good spirits with their presence. Lloyd did this better than anyone I know & every time I saw him it was the same 3 words, I MISS YOU! There hasn’t been an easy day since you left...Rest well my friend @lloydcafecadena ❤️❤️❤️

node.text:
Part 2 of this Cosplay Vlogumentary is just about complete. One of the themes of this video is The MASK👺
.
This particular clip revolves around the concept of THE MASK - a psychological concept which originated from a comic series, with a dark tone and graphic violence. The mask affects the personality of the wearer by removing all social and moral inhibitions, causing the wearer to ultimately become insane. The character was actually inspired by a combination of the Joker and the Creeper (steve ditko) as well as Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde. Characters who wore the Mask would become dangerous with ultra-violent tendencies, even if this was not the wearer's original intention.
.
In cosplay, everyone wears a mask, but it’s effects on the individual may differ from person to person! muwahaha 😈

node.text:
After a long fun vacation together, my family finally left me… but its ok because I just joined a new family, IKEA Family! 🤗

My new family is growing so fast, but we’re still open for more. Welcoming you to the Family by registering for free at family.IKEA.com.ph or link in my bio. Get ready to have awesome benefits and exclusive event invites coming your way. Don’t forget to follow IKEA Philippines on Facebook & @ikeaphilippines here on IG.
#IKEAFamilyPH #MakeHomeCount
